üé¨ CASTING CALL ‚Äì MEN vs YN (Feature Film)

Production Title: MEN vs YN
Genre: Urban Drama / Coming-of-Age / Social Thriller
Shoot Location: Florida (or TBD)
Shoot Dates: May 2026 (Tentative)
Production Company: Toy Blackmon "Successful Toy Production"
Compensation: Credit + Copy + Pay/Deferred (Beginner-Friendly Production)
Union Status: Non-Union

MEN vs YN explores the collision between internet fame, street validation, brotherhood, and real-life consequences. We are seeking raw, authentic performers who can bring truth, vulnerability, and intensity to the screen.

LEAD ROLES

ZAY (Lead)

Age Range: 18‚Äì22
Ethnicity: Open
Build: Athletic / Stylish
Vibe: Confident, flashy, charismatic

Zay is a rising social-media star addicted to attention. Loud online, conflicted inside. He believes clout equals power until real-life pressure tests his loyalty and maturity.

Must Have:
 ‚Ä¢ Strong emotional range
 ‚Ä¢ Natural swagger
 ‚Ä¢ Ability to balance charm and vulnerability
 ‚Ä¢ Comfortable on camera & with dialogue-heavy scenes

MELO (Lead)

Age Range: 19‚Äì24
Ethnicity: Open
Build: Average / Athletic
Vibe: Calm, observant, loyal

Melo is the grounded brother of the group. He sees the danger before others do. Torn between loyalty, love, and survival, Melo carries quiet strength and emotional depth.

Must Have:
 ‚Ä¢ Subtle, powerful acting
 ‚Ä¢ Ability to portray internal conflict
 ‚Ä¢ Strong chemistry with Zay

TRIGG (Lead Supporting)

Age Range: 16‚Äì19
Ethnicity: Open
Build: Slim / Lean
Vibe: Introverted, sharp, creative

Trigg is a lost kid with talent. From stealing speakers to finding his voice on stage, his arc is about transformation through honesty and art.

Must Have:
 ‚Ä¢ Comfortable performing spoken word / rap (original or written)
 ‚Ä¢ Emotional vulnerability
 ‚Ä¢ Natural, raw presence

ANTAGONIST ROLES

REX (Supporting)

Age Range: 20‚Äì26
Ethnicity: Open
Build: Athletic / Stocky
Vibe: Aggressive, impulsive

Rex is Kilo‚Äôs enforcer. He moves emotionally, confrontational and physical when needed.

Must Have:
 ‚Ä¢ High-energy presence
 ‚Ä¢ Comfortable with confrontation scenes

SUPPORTING ROLES

KEISHA

Age Range: 18‚Äì23
Ethnicity: Open
Vibe: Smart, loving, determined

Keisha is Melo‚Äôs girlfriend. She represents escape, growth, and the future. She challenges Melo to choose life over loyalty.

Must Have:
 ‚Ä¢ Emotional realism
 ‚Ä¢ Strong dramatic scenes

TONE (Supporting)

Age Range: 20‚Äì30
Ethnicity: Open
Build: Athletic / Solid
Vibe: Loyal, observant, grounded

Tone is part of the older, wiser layer of the neighborhood. He‚Äôs not loud, not chasing clout ‚Äî he watches, listens, and represents what maturity looks like after surviving the same streets the YNs glamorize.

In the final scene, Tone‚Äôs presence reinforces that growth doesn‚Äôt come from noise, but from consistency and community.

Must Have:
 ‚Ä¢ Natural, subtle performance
 ‚Ä¢ Strong non-verbal acting
 ‚Ä¢ Ability to play calm authority
 ‚Ä¢ Comfortable in mentor-style scenes

DAY PLAYERS / EXTRAS
 ‚Ä¢ Partygoers
 ‚Ä¢ Basketball players
 ‚Ä¢ YN teens
 ‚Ä¢ Police officers
 ‚Ä¢ Barbershop customers
 ‚Ä¢ Open mic audience
 ‚Ä¢ Gas station patrons
 ‚Ä¢ Social media followers

Age Range: 16‚Äì40
Experience: None required

SUBMISSION INFO 

To Submit:
 ‚Ä¢ Name
 ‚Ä¢ Age
 ‚Ä¢ Location
 ‚Ä¢ Role Interested In
 ‚Ä¢ Headshot / Photo
 ‚Ä¢ Acting Reel (if available)
 ‚Ä¢ Social Media (optional)

www.successfultoyproduction.com Under Casting Call
Subject Line: MEN vs YN ‚Äì Role Name

üé¨ TONE NOTE FOR ACTORS

This film is not about glorifying street life ‚Äî it‚Äôs about exposing the cost of attention, loyalty, and identity in the social-media era. We are looking for truth, not stereotypes.

üé¨ CASTING CALL ‚Äì TikTok / Facebook Video Presenter (Manchester)

We‚Äôre looking for confident, natural on-camera presenters / actors to feature in short-form, social media-style videos, filmed on set in Manchester.

This is not traditional acting ‚Äî we want people who feel comfortable talking directly to camera in a TikTok / Facebook Reels style. Think engaging, relatable, confident, and modern.

üîπ The Role

Present short, punchy scripts straight to camera

TikTok / Facebook-style delivery (15‚Äì60 seconds)

High-energy but natural ‚Äî not cheesy or overly salesy

Filmed in a studio / set environment

üîπ Ideal For

Actors, presenters, creators, or confident personalities

Anyone comfortable being themselves on camera

People who understand short-form social video

Strong communication and screen presence

üîπ What We‚Äôre Looking For

Confident speaking to camera

Clear, engaging delivery

Able to follow a script or bullet points

Professional, reliable, and adaptable

üîπ Location

üìç Manchester ‚Äì on set

üîπ How to Apply

Please send a short video (phone-recorded is absolutely fine) showing:

You speaking directly to camera

TikTok / presenter-style delivery

30‚Äì60 seconds is perfect

Example: https://vimeo.com/1119845100/ea1fd86ea4?fl=ip&fe=ec

david.s@springbokgroup.co.uk

Include:

Your name

Location

We‚Äôre reviewing submissions on a rolling basis.

items.text:
CASTING NOTICE:  Posting again for David, my filmmaker friend, who has need for a second talent.  Please respond to David (dshayatovich@gmail.com), not to me...
"I am creating a pitch deck for a pilot I‚Äôve written and I need an actress or model with extensive dramatic training to portray the pirate Anne Bonny.

The character: A young woman (20-25) natural looking Caucasian red headed Irish girl.
 
Anne, a real pirate of the Caribbean along with Mary Read (also in the shoot) was legendary for her pirating off Jamaica in the late 1600s. Anne‚Äôs character is immature, spoiled and (at first) rather uncaring as she lives her adventure at the cost of others. CASTING CALL

Title: Where He Is
Format: Narrative Short / Proof of Concept
Genre: Drama
Union Status: Non-Union
Shoot Location: TBD (Small-town / suburban) - Likely Louisville, KY and/or Owensboro, KY
Shoot Dates: TBD - Late Summer/Early Fall 2026
Compensation: Paid (TBD) + meals + copy + festival exposure

Please note: DMs will be ignored. Please follow the submission instructions at the end of this post. 

LOGLINE

After the sudden death of a fellow Navy veteran, a grieving husband and father begins to quietly unravel as his faith collides with loss, hypocrisy, and unanswered questions, forcing him to confront what belief means when certainty is gone.

PROJECT OVERVIEW

Where He Is is a restrained, character-driven drama exploring grief, doubt, and faith without easy answers. Told through intimate conversations and moments of silence, the film follows a Navy veteran navigating loss while trying to remain present for his family, even as the beliefs that once grounded him begin to slip.

This is a proof-of-concept short, designed to showcase performance, tone, and emotional depth rather than spectacle. The film prioritizes realism, subtlety, and lived-in performances. Loosely based on the writers real life experiences. 

ROLES AVAILABLE - (Character Names Subject to Change)

MARK (Lead) - Male | 30‚Äì40 | Any ethnicity

A Navy veteran, husband, and father. Mark is disciplined, functional, and emotionally guarded. Someone who knows how to keep moving even when he‚Äôs breaking inside. He is not angry at God so much as disoriented by the people who claim to speak for Him.

This role requires an actor comfortable with internalized performance, minimal dialogue, and emotional restraint. Much of Mark‚Äôs journey is conveyed through silence, posture, and small behavioral shifts.

Key traits: Grounded, observant, quietly conflicted. Carries grief without theatrics. Faithful in action, doubtful in belief.

SARAH - Female | 30‚Äì40 | Any ethnicity

Mark‚Äôs wife. Steady, compassionate, and emotionally perceptive, but not immune to doubt herself. Sarah believes, but her faith is not performative or unshakable. She is trying to support her husband while privately confronting her own uncertainty.

This role requires emotional transparency without melodrama. Sarah is not a moral counterweight, she is a partner, equally vulnerable.

Key traits: Warm but honest, Emotionally resilient, not naive. Comfortable with silence and subtle shifts.

PREACHER - Male | 55‚Äì70 | Any ethnicity

A longtime pastor who speaks gently and without ego. He is thoughtful, self-aware, and willing to admit failure. He does not offer answers, only honesty. This character should feel like someone who has lived through regret, not someone performing wisdom.

This role benefits from an actor who can convey gravitas through stillness and allow uncertainty to live in the pauses.

Key traits: Calm, reflective, humble. Comfortable admitting ‚ÄúI don‚Äôt know‚Äù. Authority without control.

DAVID - Male | 30‚Äì40 | Any ethnicity (Day Player)

A fellow Navy veteran and close friend of the deceased. David is sincere, grounded, and emotionally open in a way Mark isn‚Äôt, yet. He represents belief as survival rather than doctrine.

Key traits: Quiet strength, Emotionally accessible, Deep sense of brotherhood.

KIDS (2 roles)

Any gender | Ages 6‚Äì9 | Any ethnicity

Mark and Sarah‚Äôs children. Natural, curious, and emotionally perceptive. These roles are small but important, innocent questions carry heavy weight.

SUBMISSION INSTRUCTIONS:

Actors interested in submitting should email: skaldsagastudios@gmail.com

Subject Line: Where He Is ‚Äì [Role] ‚Äì [Actor‚Äôs Name]

Please include: Resume, Headshots, Demo reel (if available)

Submission Deadline: Friday, February 13th @ 10:00 PM EST

Selected actors will be contacted with audition details.

üçí **CASTING CALL: University of Westminster Graduation Short Film (LONDON)**

***CHERRY ON TOP***** ‚Äî Black & surreal comedy-drama with surrealist elements**

Shooting in London between **Feb 14 ‚Äì March 5** (exact dates TBC) 

5 consecutive shoot days

***Cherry on Top*** is a contained, actor-driven short film exploring emotional decay, morality, denial, and social performance through deadpan absurdity, surrealism, and escalating discomfort.

At a carefully orchestrated dinner party, two couples lose their manners as a wine-fuelled confession of infidelity exposes a far more destabilising secret. 

Throughout the film, a cooked duck on the dinner table slowly rots in plain view, completely ignored by the characters.

Performance style: **grounded, restrained, subtext-driven**. Think long silences, polite cruelty, sustained social tension.

**Catherine (Lead)**
Playing age: **30s‚Äì40s**
The dinner party hostess and Hugh‚Äôs wife. Elegant, intelligent, self-righteous, and controlling. Catherine has meticulously curated her life and believes she is emotionally evolved. As the evening unfolds, her composure slowly fractures, revealing unresolved issues and a quietly devious desperation beneath the polish.
A role requiring precision, stillness, restraint, and a slow, unsettling unravel.

**Hugh (Supporting)**
Playing age: **30s‚Äì40s**
Catherine‚Äôs husband. Timid, gentle, and emotionally reserved, Hugh avoids confrontation and retreats into routine and wine. Deeply likeable and sensitive, he is often overshadowed‚Äîuntil his passivity gives way to something unexpectedly dark.
Played with sincerity and understatement, allowing the absurdity to emerge naturally.

**This role includes an intense, scripted makeout scene with Ingrid. An intimacy coordinator will be present.*

**Ingrid (LEAD)**
Playing age: **30s‚Äì40s**
Alec‚Äôs wife. Obsessive, competitive, and emotionally volatile beneath a polished exterior. Preoccupied with youth, validation, and social hierarchy‚Äîespecially in comparison to Catherine. Passive-aggressive, smug, and deeply insecure.
Midway through the film, a private bathroom moment exposes her fragility as she spirals alone with her reflection.
A demanding role rooted in desperation masquerading as confidence.

**This role includes an intense, scripted makeout scene with Hugh. An intimacy coordinator will be present.*

* This is a non-paid final-year University of Westminster production. Food and transport will be provided. Credit and showreel-quality footage guaranteed. The film may be submitted to festivals.

To apply: 

Please DM or email **cherryontop.grad.film@gmail.com **with your showreel (if available) and the role(s) you‚Äôre applying for.

Open to London-based actors or those able to self-travel.

Feel free to share and thank you! üçí

Shooting in London between **Feb 14 ‚Äì March 5** (exact dates TBC) 

5 consecutive shoot days

***Cherry on Top*** is a contained, actor-driven short film exploring emotional decay, morality, denial, and social performance through deadpan absurdity, surrealism, and escalating discomfort.

At a carefully orchestrated dinner party, two couples lose their manners as a wine-fuelled confession of infidelity exposes a far more destabilising secret. 

Throughout the film, a cooked duck on the dinner table slowly rots in plain view, completely ignored by the characters.

Performance style: **grounded, restrained, subtext-driven**. Think long silences, polite cruelty, sustained social tension.

**Catherine (Lead)**
Playing age: **30s‚Äì40s**
The dinner party hostess and Hugh‚Äôs wife. Elegant, intelligent, self-righteous, and controlling. Catherine has meticulously curated her life and believes she is emotionally evolved. As the evening unfolds, her composure slowly fractures, revealing unresolved issues and a quietly devious desperation beneath the polish.
A role requiring precision, stillness, restraint, and a slow, unsettling unravel.

**Hugh (Supporting)**
Playing age: **30s‚Äì40s**
Catherine‚Äôs husband. Timid, gentle, and emotionally reserved, Hugh avoids confrontation and retreats into routine and wine. Deeply likeable and sensitive, he is often overshadowed‚Äîuntil his passivity gives way to something unexpectedly dark.
Played with sincerity and understatement, allowing the absurdity to emerge naturally.

**This role includes an intense, scripted makeout scene with Ingrid. An intimacy coordinator will be present.*

**Ingrid (LEAD)**
Playing age: **30s‚Äì40s**
Alec‚Äôs wife. Obsessive, competitive, and emotionally volatile beneath a polished exterior. Preoccupied with youth, validation, and social hierarchy‚Äîespecially in comparison to Catherine. Passive-aggressive, smug, and deeply insecure.
Midway through the film, a private bathroom moment exposes her fragility as she spirals alone with her reflection.
A demanding role rooted in desperation masquerading as confidence.

**This role includes an intense, scripted makeout scene with Hugh. An intimacy coordinator will be present.*

* This is a non-paid final-year University of Westminster production. Food and transport will be provided. Credit and showreel-quality footage guaranteed. The film may be submitted to festivals.

To apply: 

Please DM or email **cherryontop.grad.film@gmail.com **with your showreel (if available) and the role(s) you‚Äôre applying for.

Open to London-based actors or those able to self-travel.

Feel free to share and thank you! üçí

My dear uncle, a devoted family man and a beloved member of his community, has recently moved into a nursing home. Saying goodbye to the home he built over so many years has been incredibly difficult for all of us.

Hi Jackson. Welcome to London! I've taken a look at your showreel. It's currently too long - CDs are busy people. I recommend you go through it and choose the strongest nuggets. Feel free to internally edit the individual clips, so that the focus is on you not the other actors. And it would be better to have separate reels for drama and commercials, rather than mixing them. A good way to connect with industry professionals is by joining Act on This, the TV actors' network. I've been a member for two years and have found it really helpful with guidance on "the business of the business". They have weekly Zoom calls with agents, casting directors, actors, etc who share their contact details. Here's a taste of what's coming up in the next few weeks. ## **CASTING CALL: Background Talent (Non-Union)**

**Project:** *Alchemy In Venice* (Indie Feature Film)

**Location:** Venice, CA (On-location)

**Dates:** February 17th ‚Äì February 23rd, 2026

**Rate:** $50/day Stipend + Meal + Credit
**The Project**

*Alchemy In Venice* is a soulful, atmospheric indie feature capturing the vibrant and eclectic spirit of Venice Beach. We are looking for authentic locals and fresh faces to bring our world to life.
**Who We Are Looking For**
* **Adult Men & Women (21+):** All ethnicities, shapes, and styles. We want the true "Venice" vibe‚Äîartists, surfers, techies, tourists, and everyone in between.
* **Bilingual Talent:** Huge plus! (Please specify which languages you speak in your submission).
* **Availability:** Must be local to Los Angeles or able to work as a local hire in Venice.
**Submission Instructions**

Please send the following to **jcj248@gmail.com** with the subject line: **ALCH_Background_[Your Name]**
1. Two recent photos (one headshot/selfie, one full-body look).
2. Your general availability between Feb 17‚Äì23.
3. Any special skills (skating, surfing, playing an instrument, etc.).
4. Confirmation that you are non-union.
## **Perks include:**
* **Professional BTS Stills of you/your character in the scene.**
* **Invitation To The Wrap Party**
* **IMDb Credit**
* **Healthy and Sustainable Crafty **
* **Parking reimbursement (if applicable)**

LACAE Theatre and School Open House is this Saturday from 1-4 PM! Mini-workshops, an Actor's Career Mindset talk, Q&A and pizza! All free with RSVP. 

* [https://www.la-cae.org/event-list](https://www.la-cae.org/event-list) (RSVP here)

**Details: **
Event starts right at 1:00 PM and goes to 4:00 PM. We suggest that you plan on being there the full day to get the most from the programming.
* Address: 11031 Camarillo Street, North Hollywood, CA 91602
* Free Street Parking Available. Give yourself enough time to park and walk over. 
* Our entrance is on the side gate to the left of St. Matthew's Church. (Please note that we are not affiliated with the church.)
* Pizza and drinks will be provided. If you have any dietary restrictions, we suggest that you bring your own snacks. 
* Wear comfortable clothing, shoes you can move in, and bring a water bottle!

Mitch, an obsessive feng shui specialist who cleanses homes contaminated by negative energy, discovers an invisible stain while renovating an old house ‚Äî a stain that awakens a hidden entity each time he tries to erase it.

Requires precision, restraint, strong internal acting.

Grounded, observant assistant who witnesses Mitch‚Äôs psychological collapse.

CASTING CALL ‚Äì PAID LEAD ROLE (SHORT FILM)

Hi everyone!

I‚Äôm a film student at the University of Brighton, and I‚Äôm currently casting the lead role in my graduation short film, *Interference*.

William Rayner ‚Äì male, age flexible (playing 45-60)

This is a largely internal role with minimal dialogue. We‚Äôre looking for a grounded, naturalistic performance, subtle, lived-in, and emotionally contained rather than theatrical.

The role involves acting opposite a stop-motion character, which will be added in post-production. On set, stand-ins will be used for eyeline and blocking, and performers will be fully supported throughout the process.

PAY & PRACTICALS:

Paid role (¬£100 per day, 8-hour maximum day with breaks) 

Shoot length: 4‚Äì5 days.

Shoot location: Sussex (Hastings & Lewes).

Dates: Late February / early March (flexible based on your schedule within 21 Feb ‚Äì 29 Mar).

Travel & accommodation fully covered (Airbnb provided).

PRODUCTION INFO:

This is an independent student short film produced as part of my graduation project at the University of Brighton. We plan to submit the finished film to UK and international film festivals.

If this sounds like something you‚Äôd be interested in, feel free to send us an email (interferenceshort@gmail.com), comment or DM, and I‚Äôll send over the full casting package with some more information.

Thanks so much!

Elsie Gregory ‚Äì Writer/Director

**CASTING SHOUT-OUT ‚Äî FEATURE ARTISTS (60+)**

We‚Äôre seeking two brilliant character actors (playing age 60+) to appear as a playful ‚ÄúRomeo & Juliet‚Äù duo in the spirit of Compo & Nora Batty (Last of the Summer Wine) for a one-day scene in our Yorkshire-based feature film. This cameo will with our main cast, a handful of lines each, and plenty of cheeky northern charm.

**Details**

Roles:** ‚ÄúRomeo‚Äù & ‚ÄúJuliet‚Äù (feature artists, a few lines each)
Vibe:** Warm, witty, gently combative banter, think mismatched soulmates with decades of history, twinkle in the eye and spark in the step
Equity** rates (Feature Artist)

* Finalists may be asked for a short self-tape

CASTING CALL: Surrealist Short Film "BEANS" - Shoots in Twyford/Winchester
We are looking for four actors to join our upcoming short film, "BEANS," a stylised look at the chaotic, wonderful world of a local coffee shop. Beans is our final university project, and we‚Äôre putting everything we‚Äôve got into it to ensure we end our film production journey with a bang!

PROJECT DETAILS:

-Type: Student Short Film

-Dates: 23rd ‚Äì 29th March (Evening/Night shoots: 5:00 PM ‚Äì 10:30 PM)

-Location: Twyford (near Winchester), Hampshire

-Requirements: Must be local to Hampshire.

-Compensation: Travel costs covered + Food provided. Full credit and a high-quality copy of the film for your reel.

ROLES NEEDED:

JOEL (30s): Scruffy, tired, and tech-nerdy. He has the "personality of a houseplant" and a very specific coffee order (5 sugars!).

MR. HARPER / GORDON (Mid 30s- 40s): Tall, preppy, and wealthy. A man of high status who eventually ends up dressed as Tarzan as his wild nature comes to surface. Needs great physical comedy and a commanding presence.

TODD (40-60s): A charming, scruffy man down on his luck. A "few screws loose" but very kind. Must be comfortable with a high-energy Elvis impersonation and dance moves.

OLD LEO (60s-70s): The older version of our protagonist. Warm, contented, and wise. He shares a beautiful, grounding moment with his wife, Adele.

HOW TO APPLY: Please send your headshot, reel (if available), and which role you are interested in to millainakemp@gmail.com or DM directly! Follow us on @beans.short on Instagram for behind the scenes!

May be an image of text that says 'RICH (able to play 21). 21) Quiet. Introspective. Stuck. A recent graduate drowning in job rejections and debt. Rich spends his days applying for jobs and waiting for replies that never come. Debt and expectation weigh heavily, turning the city into something both vast and claustrophobic. Quiet, emotionally restrained and deeply human. Lead role'

May be an image of text that says 'Alfie (able to play 21) Where Rich hesitates, Alfie charges ahead. Fueled by self-help myths and American pop culture, he's S convinced they' re one idea away from success. Every failure is just another lesson. Charismatic, fast t-talking, and endlessly optimistic -with a vulnerability he refuses to acknowledge. Funny, restless, and quietly tragic. Lead role'

May be an image of text that says 'Irene (20s-30s). The other half of The Ilene & Irene Show. .Irene is Ilene's equally glamorous co-host, dressed in teal, maintaining the same performative cheer and TV brightness. Together they represent the artificial optimism of self-help culture, their exaggerated energy a reflection of the false promises they sell. Note:A A small supporting role, approximately half a day of filming (28th Feb)'

FOUNDING MEMBERS WANTED: Professional Mourners | Paid Ongoing Work | Nationwide

MournMate ‚Äî the first marketplace connecting professional mourners with families and funeral homes ‚Äî is building our founding network.

The first 500 mourners to join will receive FOUNDING MEMBER status with priority visibility, early access to premium bookings, and recognition as the professionals who built this platform from the ground up.

Ideal for:
‚úì Actors seeking flexible, meaningful paid work
‚úì Musicians (vocalists, pianists, bagpipers, etc.)
‚úì Public speakers & eulogy writers
‚úì Anyone with cultural or religious ceremony experience

Compensation: $25‚Äì$300+/hr based on your skills and tier
Set your own rates and schedule
Emergency bookings pay +50% bonus
Get paid via secure direct deposit after each service

This isn't background work. This is real performance ‚Äî holding space, providing comfort, and honoring lives with dignity.

Requirements:
Pass ID verification
Own formal attire
Professional, compassionate demeanor

Sign up now before Founding Member spots fill: www.mournmate.com ‚Üí "Become a Mourner"

We‚Äôre currently casting for the lead roles for a Manchester-based proof of concept short film shooting Feb/March.

attachments.ocrText: May be an image of text that says 'RICH (able to play 21). 21) Quiet. Introspective. Stuck. A recent graduate drowning in job rejections and debt. Rich spends his days applying for jobs and waiting for replies that never come. Debt and expectation weigh heavily, turning the city into something both vast and claustrophobic. Quiet, emotionally restrained and deeply human. Lead role'

May be an image of text that says 'Ilene (20s-30s) One half of The Ilene & Irene Show; an upbeat, American-style talk show Chad stumbles across while channel surfing. Ilene is polished and composed, always performing for the camera. She's dressed head to- toe in pink, smiling as if her life depends on it. The role captures the glossy absurdity of media perfection and how it contrasts with the reality of the characters watching it. Note: A small supporting role, approximately half a day of filming (28th Feb)'

May be an image of text that says 'Irene (20s-30s). The other half of The Ilene & Irene Show. .Irene is Ilene's equally glamorous co-host, dressed in teal, maintaining the same performative cheer and TV brightness. Together they represent the artificial optimism of self-help culture, their exaggerated energy a reflection of the false promises they sell. Note:A A small supporting role, approximately half a day of filming (28th Feb)'

May be an image of text that says 'Alfie (able to play 21) Where Rich hesitates, Alfie charges ahead. Fueled by self-help myths and American pop culture, he's S convinced they' re one idea away from success. Every failure is just another lesson. Charismatic, fast t-talking, and endlessly optimistic -with a vulnerability he refuses to acknowledge. Funny, restless, and quietly tragic. Lead role'

May be a graphic of studying and text that says 'o Apply: Self-tape -T deadline: Sun 8th Feb ‚Ä¢In-person chemistry reads mid-Feb Feb Script sides available via link in Land on the Feet insta bio Submit self-tape to: ladonthefet.productions@gmail.c Include: Name/ Age/ Role(s) applying for Instincts > polish'

Visual Illusion & LED Performance Art
I am a performance artist from Vietnam, specializing in visual illusion, LED illusion arts, and unique physical performances.

I am eager to bring my art to stages, events, and festivals around the world.

If you are looking for something distinctive, elegant, and visually powerful, let‚Äôs connect.

sharedPost.text:
Liebe Produktionen, Produzenten aber auch liebe Agenturen und Filmschaffende in Deutschland:

+++ Der  erste Gagenkatalog f√ºr Kompars*innen und Kleindarsteller*innen ist seit ein paar Tagen √∂ffentlich! +++

Die darin angegebenen Betr√§ge sind Empfehlungen der Initiative Faire Gagen und beruhen auf den Erfahrungen vieler etablierter Filmschaffender und ihren R√ºckmeldungen an unsere Initiative, als auch auf Gespr√§che unsererseits mit Agenturen und Produktionen. 
 
Dabei werden auch schrittweise gew√§hlte Ziele des Katalogs (z.B. von budget-schw√§cheren Produktionen) zu mehr Fairness und damit auch wieder zu h√∂herer Motivation der Filmschaffenden f√ºhren.

Nachweislich kommt es gerade durch etablierte Filmschaffende zu weniger Problemen beim Buchungsprocedere und ganz besonders am Set, als bei st√§ndig neu gecasteten Menschen, die eben oft ganz andere Beweggr√ºnde haben, wie z.B. "einfach mal dabei sein" und dies auch selbst f√ºr eigentlich nicht mehr Faire Gagen. 

Dazu jedoch nur als Beispiel, die bekanntlich  immer h√∂her steigende Zahl von kurzfristigen Buchungs-Absagen und dabei besonders das Nichterscheinen am Drehort ohne Absage, festgebuchter Kompars*innen. 
Besonders letzteres sehen selbstverst√§ndlich auch wir als ein absolutes "No Go" gegen√ºber unseren Produktionen und Agenturen an.

+++ Eine faire Bezahlung aber auch das schrittweise Umdenken bez√ºglich veralteter Setregeln, oder kaum noch nachvollziebarer Buchungsbeschr√§nkungen (Beispiel Altersgrenzen) wird, verbunden mit  einer h√∂heren Wertsch√§tzung gegen√ºber den Filmschaffenden,  nicht nur zu  einem besseren Arbeitsklima f√ºhren, sondern zwangsl√§ufig auch ein Garant f√ºr direkte  Zeit- und Kosteneinsparungen der Produktionen sein. +++

Auch die Agenturen k√∂nnten so zumindest bei dem f√ºr jede Produktion so wichtigen Faktor "Zeit" profitieren und so noch effizienter und professioneller f√ºr ihre zu betreuenden Produktionen arbeiten.
Tats√§chlich werden nur so beide Seiten mittel- und langfristig provitieren. 
Der leider oft voreilig eingesetzte  Rotstift mancher Produktionen hat bereits viele etablierte und zuverl√§ssige Filmschaffende in den letzten  Jahren zwangsl√§ufig verprellt. 

Daher sehen wir auch ganz allgemein, dass eine Philosophie von "Einsparungen" und "Weiter so" (auf einem sich nicht mehr lohnenden Gagen-Niveau) dem deutschen Film eher schaden als n√ºtzen wird.
Produktionen, die sich eh schon an faire Gagen und Zuschl√§ge halten sind hier nat√ºrlich weniger angesprochen. Sie dienen f√ºr uns jedoch als absolut beispielhaft f√ºr alle anderen, denn sie zeigen uns schon seit vielen Jahren sehr eindrucksvoll, dass Fairness und Wertsch√§tzung eben doch ganz einfach funktioniert.

Initiative Faire Gagen.

Call for Entries to the CITTADOR INTERNATIONAL FILM FESTIVAL!

We‚Äôre approaching our first deadline of the season, and we‚Äôre officially calling on filmmakers from around the world to submit their work to the Cittador International Film Festival (CIFF)!

This year is extra special: Cittador IFF celebrates its 5th anniversary - our first milestone ‚Äî and we would love to celebrate it together with you and your films.

Cittador IFF is dedicated to showcasing and awarding outstanding independent cinema based solely on artistic quality. Free from commercial constraints, we celebrate films that are bold, original, imaginative, and inspiring - stories that live beyond the mainstream, regardless of genre, background, age, or filmmaking experience.
Our international jury carefully evaluates every submission. Selected and award-winning films receive a public jury statement, highlighting what makes each work unique and meaningful. Award-winning films will be screened in front of an international audience in the famous CineCenter Cinema in Vienna.

We also empower filmmakers to share their voices: selected filmmakers can submit a written interview to be published in the official festival catalog ‚Äî whether award-winning or not.

Submit now via Filmfreeway, Festhome or TouJiang.

Be part of our journey. Be part of our anniversary.
Submit your film and celebrate independent cinema with CIFF!

https://cittador-iff.com

 #cittadorinternationalfilmfestival #callforentries #filmfestival #cittadoriff

Are you an independent filmmaker ready to showcase your work on an international stage? The Cittador International Film Festival (CIFF) in Vienna celebrates inspiration, creativity, and uniqueness in cinema.

Our video ‚ÄúCITTADOR, my CITTADOR! ‚Äì Winged Words‚Äù captures the festival‚Äôs spirit and philosophy ‚Äì highlighting what makes CIFF stand out as a platform for true artistic expression.

Based on the book CITTADOR, my CITTADOR! ‚Äì Winged Words by Ana Bilic, this video reflects the core values that guide the festival‚Äôs film selection: artistic vision, originality, and emotional impact.

Submit your film today and join a global community of storytellers who think differently.

items.text:
CASTING - BLOOD & PAPER

Genre: Drama, Coming of Age

Synopsis: After a violent altercation leaves her suspended from school, anger-prone Demi becomes obsessed with obtaining her Tribal ID to prove that she belongs somewhere. But as her need to protect others pushes them farther away, she must confront the realization that identity is not something you can find on a piece of paper.

Roles:

DEMI: (Late teens/early 20‚Äôs, Female, Black/African Descent, Racially Ambiguous, Lead)

A high schooler with anger issues, a lack of friends, but a fierce loyalty to protect those around her. None of her emotions come with a middle ground: when she‚Äôs sad, she‚Äôs inconsolable, when she‚Äôs angry, she‚Äôs furious. Ends up pushing people away due to this nature. Begins an obsessive attempt to obtain her Tribal ID in hopes that it will make her feel like she belongs somewhere.

LENA: (Late teens/early 20‚Äôs, Female, Any Ethnicity, Supporting)

Demi‚Äôs Older Sister. Loves and cares for Demi, but secretly holds some resentment towards the problem child that is her sister. She is moving across the country for college, and is worried how Demi will do without her there.

ADRIAN: (Late teens/early 20‚Äôs, Male, Native American/Indigenous Descent, Hispanic/Latino, Supporting)

An attractive, native farm hand, and childhood best friend of Demi. He admires her protective nature, and has always had a crush on her .. though Demi has always been too oblivious to notice.

DRUNKARDS: (20-30, Male, Any Ethnicity)

Two drunk men on the street who catcall Lena, not realizing that doing so will incur the wrath of Demi. 

Production Company: Nymesis Studios, Dir. Corinne Nuncio

Production Type: Student Film

Contact Information: Corinne@nymesisstudios.com, please reach out with headshot and resume for sides. (If you don‚Äôt have a headshot or resume, please reach out for sides regardless)

Use BLOOD & PAPER - ROLE in your email header.

Run Time: Short

Compensation: Unpaid. Footage provided, final copy of film provided, meals provided.

Union Status: Non-Union

Audition Information: Virtual, Self Tape auditions due by Saturday, February 7th. Submit to Corinne@nymesisstudios.com. In-person callback date, early-mid February.

Shooting Schedule: Shoots 6-7 days, March 8-14. Planned rehearsal dates in late February, early March.

Filming Location: Sedalia, Denver, Aurora

Project Description: We will be shooting on a ranch around real animals (specifically horses and cows), please be aware for any possible allergies.

ISO NON-UNION BACKGROUND TALENT FOR ‚Äú*PANKCAKE SKANK*,‚Äù a punk-inflected, surreal short film set in a neon, always-night world where a pancake-thieving outlaw disrupts the lives of everyone she crosses paths with.

SHOOT DATES: February 16-21st

LOCATION: Las Vegas 

We‚Äôre building a sci-fi punk universe and looking for visually striking, unconventional performers with strong character energy. Distinct physical traits, bold style, and unique presence are highly encouraged. All genders, body types, and backgrounds welcome. Queer- and LGBTQ+-friendly set.

**Featured Background (PAID):**

‚Ä¢ **Nuclear Family** ‚Äì Mom & Dad (30‚Äì40s), Daughter & Son (8‚Äì13)

*Shoots Saturday, 2/21.* Must be comfortable with special effects maple syrup on wardrobe/skin. It is a plus if you are a real family willing to work together.

‚Ä¢ **Teenage Girlfriend (18‚Äì29)** ‚Äì *Shoots 2/17 overnight, subject to change.* Must be comfortable with special effects maple syrup.

‚Ä¢ **Teenage Boyfriend (18‚Äì29)** ‚Äì *Shoots 2/17 overnight, subject to change.* Must be comfortable with special effects maple syrup.

‚Ä¢ **Child with Hair (9‚Äì13)** ‚Äì *Shoots 2/17 overnight, subject to change.* Must be comfortable with special effects maple syrup.

‚Ä¢ **Hostess (30‚Äì45)** ‚Äì Directed physical interaction, no dialogue. *Shoots 2/20, tentative.*

‚Ä¢ **Drag Queens** ‚Äì Strong presence and style encouraged. *Shoots 2/16, subject to change.*

**Background (UNPAID):**

‚Ä¢ Diner / Waffle House Patrons (Ages 18‚Äì101)

‚Ä¢ Waiter

‚Ä¢ Line Cook / Staff

‚Ä¢ LGBTQIA+ Bar Patrons

‚Ä¢ Police (25‚Äì40)

Background roles may work one or multiple days between February 16‚Äì21. Availability across these dates is important, though you are not required for all days. All performers will receive screen credit and meals during their work day.

If you‚Äôre interested, please fill out this google form: [https://forms.gle/WoGYUNZX8WGtjqJJA](https://forms.gle/WoGYUNZX8WGtjqJJA) 

If you have any questions please feel free to reach us at **[pancakeskankcasting@gmail.com](mailto:pancakeskankcasting@gmail.com)**.

Thank you!

We‚Äôre building a sci-fi punk universe and looking for visually striking, unconventional performers with strong character energy. Distinct physical traits, bold style, and unique presence are highly encouraged. All genders, body types, and backgrounds welcome. Queer- and LGBTQ+-friendly set.

**Featured Background (PAID):**

‚Ä¢ **Nuclear Family** ‚Äì Mom & Dad (30‚Äì40s), Daughter & Son (8‚Äì13)

*Shoots Saturday, 2/21.* Must be comfortable with special effects maple syrup on wardrobe/skin. It is a plus if you are a real family willing to work together.

‚Ä¢ **Teenage Girlfriend (18‚Äì29)** ‚Äì *Shoots 2/17 overnight, subject to change.* Must be comfortable with special effects maple syrup.

‚Ä¢ **Teenage Boyfriend (18‚Äì29)** ‚Äì *Shoots 2/17 overnight, subject to change.* Must be comfortable with special effects maple syrup.

‚Ä¢ **Child with Hair (9‚Äì13)** ‚Äì *Shoots 2/17 overnight, subject to change.* Must be comfortable with special effects maple syrup.

‚Ä¢ **Hostess (30‚Äì45)** ‚Äì Directed physical interaction, no dialogue. *Shoots 2/20, tentative.*

‚Ä¢ **Drag Queens** ‚Äì Strong presence and style encouraged. *Shoots 2/16, subject to change.*

**Background (UNPAID):**

‚Ä¢ Diner / Waffle House Patrons (Ages 18‚Äì101)

‚Ä¢ Waiter

‚Ä¢ Line Cook / Staff

‚Ä¢ LGBTQIA+ Bar Patrons

‚Ä¢ Police (25‚Äì40)

Background roles may work one or multiple days between February 16‚Äì21. Availability across these dates is important, though you are not required for all days. All performers will receive screen credit and meals during their work day.

If you‚Äôre interested, please fill out this google form: [https://forms.gle/WoGYUNZX8WGtjqJJA](https://forms.gle/WoGYUNZX8WGtjqJJA) 

If you have any questions please feel free to reach us at **[pancakeskankcasting@gmail.com](mailto:pancakeskankcasting@gmail.com)**.

Thank you!

items.text:
PAID OPPORTUNITY
We are casting an actress (35-45 playing age) for the role of Janice in our 10-minute student short film Elvis Died for This.

Set in 1985, the Wright family are barely holding it together. When the youngest son, Mikey, accidentally blows up their neighbour's beloved guinea pig, Elvis, in a homemade science experiment, the family scrambles to cover it up. As the chaos unravels, Mikey finally tells the truth - about the guinea pig, and about how broken his family really is. His honesty forces everyone to face reality, and the Wrights finally stop pretending to be a happy family.

No prior acting experience is required, so if this is something you are interested in, please do not hesitate to apply.

Shooting dates:

7/03/2026

14/03/2026

21/03/2026

22/03/2026

Applicants must be based in or near Falmouth, or close enough to travel to and from Falmouth each shooting weekend.

To apply or for more information email - eb300109@falmouth.ac.uk

**CASTING CALL: PROFESSOR WILLARD**

**Supporting Role | SCAD Senior Thesis Film // *****Opulence***

**March 5-8th, 2026 | Savannah, GA**

**Logline: **

When a Black woman becomes exhausted by passive-aggressive racism at her college, she finds inspiration and connection through a myth of Black angels sent by God.

**Professor Willard (Late 30‚Äôs-50‚Äôs, White, Male):** 

A public speaking professor at Grove Technical College for five years, originally from a small town in Michigan, now living in the DMV after relocating for his wife, Iyla (African American), who works in D.C. Willard is passionate, articulate, and well-meaning; he teaches with enthusiasm, mentors his students, and doesn‚Äôt tolerate disrespect, yet struggles to speak up publicly when racism and microaggressions arise. He privately supports Myra but hesitates within institutional systems. Outside of work, he enjoys quiet nights with his wife, debating over coffee (one sugar), and taking samba classes on Tuesday nights. The role explores the tension between genuine allyship and passive complicity; not a white savior.

**Contact:**

Producer | Hannah Ballard // hballard9hb@gmail.com

Director | Music Miranda // mmiran21@student.scad.edu

*Please submit a headshot and resum√© via email for more information.  *

*credit & copy of the film comp.

*** CASTING CALL FOR STUDENT SHORT - UNPAID (OTHER BENEFITS) - See below ***

Hi everyone,

I‚Äôm currently casting for an 8-10 minute student short film ‚Äò**ONEIROPHOBIA**‚Äô, a psychological drama that explores trauma, guilt, and the fear of dreaming. The story follows a young man, Liam, who is haunted by recurring nightmares connected to the death of his younger brother, until a therapist/oneirologist begins to help him unravel these dark visions. The film delves into themes of family conflict, grief, mental health, and trauma.

We‚Äôre looking to cast 4 characters:
1. **LIAM DAY **(Male | Playing Age: 18-24 | Any Ethnicity | Lead Role)
2. **ROBERT/ROBYN (‚ÄòROB‚Äô) WALKER **(Any Gender | Playing Age: 40-50 | Any Ethnicity | Supporting Role)
3. **LESLIE DAY **(Female | Voice Over | Any Ethnicity | Supporting Role)
4. **THE RUNNER **(Male | Playing Age: 20-30 | Any Ethnicity | Supporting Role)

**Shoot Details:**
The film will be shot over five days but the different roles will be required on different days. Liam is the only role that would be required on all days. All filming will take place in and around Glasgow and is scheduled for weekdays between 16th-24th March 2026 (exact dates TBC).

**Pay and compensation:**
Please note that this is a **no-budget student short film**. While we‚Äôre unable to offer payment, we‚Äôre committed to ensuring that all actors gain meaningful value from this opportunity. All cast members will receive f**ootage from the final edit for use in their showreels** (and we‚Äôre happy to assist with cutting this if needed). We‚Äôre also currently working to arrange **complimentary headshots** and high-quality **BTS pics** for successful applicants. In addition, cast will benefit from an inclusive and enjoyable on-set experience, as well as potential exposure should the film be submitted to festivals in the future. This opportunity is particularly well suited to those who are new to the industry and looking to build or expand their showreel.

**How to Apply:**
Please email a **headshot or recent photo** and your **showreel or performance clips** (if available) to ReeseODonnell6@gmail.com and 30508450@cityofglacol.ac.uk with the subject:

‚Äú**Oneirophobia ‚Äì [Character Name] ‚Äì [Your Name]**‚Äù

Application deadline is **21:30**, **8th February 2026.**

Audition sides will be provided on call back.

We guarantee a professional, respectful, enjoyable, and collaborative set and would love to have you on the team.

We look forward to hearing from you!

In addition, cast will benefit from an inclusive and enjoyable on-set experience, as well as potential exposure should the film be submitted to festivals in the future. This opportunity is particularly well suited to those who are new to the industry and looking to build or expand their showreel.

**How to Apply:**
Please email a **headshot or recent photo** and your **showreel or performance clips** (if available) to ReeseODonnell6@gmail.com and 30508450@cityofglacol.ac.uk with the subject:

‚Äú**Oneirophobia ‚Äì [Character Name] ‚Äì [Your Name]**‚Äù

Application deadline is **21:30**, **8th February 2026.**

Audition sides will be provided on call back.

We guarantee a professional, respectful, enjoyable, and collaborative set and would love to have you on the team.

We look forward to hearing from you!

Model | Performer | Wellness Professional
With over 80+ professional photoshoots under my belt ‚Äî including paid projects across fashion, lifestyle, artistic, body paint, and life modeling ‚Äî I have developed a versatile presence in front of the camera backed by a disciplined lifestyle and unique skillset. 

Height    195 cm  | 6.5
Weight  85kg | 187 pounds
Neck      40 cm  | 15.7 |
Chest    102 cm  | 40.2 |
Waist     78 cm  | 30.7 |
Hips.  96 cm |  37 |
Sleeve   81 | cm  | 31.9 |
Inseam   81 | cm  | 31.9 |
Shoe Size  45  EU   | 10.5 UK
Skin Tone: Medium-light  
Eye Color: Brown 
Hair color: Dark brown 

Alongside modeling, I bring on-screen experience from multiple TV shows, interview formats, podcasts, and extra appearances in my home country, while continuously expanding into acting and performance-based work. 

Performance Skills
‚Ä¢ Aerial Acrobatics ‚Äî Hoop, Trapeze, Silks, Rope (Beginner‚ÄìIntermediate)
‚Ä¢ Contact staff ‚Äî Intermediate
‚Ä¢ Staff spinning - Intermediate 
‚Ä¢ Katana/Aikido - Intermediate 
‚Ä¢ Yoga ‚Äî Advanced
‚Ä¢ Swimming ‚Äî Advanced
‚Ä¢ Parkour - Intermediate+
‚Ä¢ Dance - freestyle freedom of expression intuitive improvised movement 
Some stage combat, shooting, falling experience 

Professional Background
‚Ä¢ Qualified Swimming Coach, Yoga Teacher, and Personal Trainer with 14+ years of teaching experience.
‚Ä¢ Deep expertise in health, movement, breath, wellness, and high performance. 

What Sets Me Apart
‚Ä¢ Strong work ethic, relentless discipline, and ability to perform under discomfort, pressure, and challenging conditions.
‚Ä¢ Holistic approach to self-regulation ‚Äî always camera-ready, physically prepared, mentally sharp, and adaptable.
‚Ä¢ Highly motivated in building my craft and presence ‚Äî I create, edit, and post content daily across YouTube, TikTok, and Instagram to develop audience. 

Seeking opportunities in modeling, acting, and performance ‚Äî primarily in the UK, but open to international projects.
22

**Castingaufruf f√ºr studentischen Kurzfilm (T√ºbinale)**

Meine studentische Filmgruppe sucht Darsteller*innen f√ºr einen ca. 6-min√ºtigen Kurzfilm, der im Rahmen der T√ºbinale entsteht. Gedreht wird in der Fildergegend nahe Stuttgart. Der genaue Drehzeitraum wird noch bekannt gegeben.

**Logline:**
Als eine junge Frau beginnt, ihre Beziehung mit einem anderen Paar zu vergleichen, verliert sie den Blick f√ºr die Liebe, die direkt vor ihr steht.

**Gesuchte Rollen (alle ca. 19‚Äì25 Jahre):**

**Weibliche Hauptrolle**
Junge Frau in ihrer ersten ernsthaften Beziehung. Unsicher, emotional offen, stark von √§u√üeren Erwartungen und Vergleichen beeinflusst. Die Rolle erfordert ein sensibles Spiel innerer Konflikte und leiser emotionaler Ver√§nderungen.

**M√§nnliche Hauptrolle**
Ihr Freund. Bodenst√§ndig, ruhig und bem√ºht. Er liebt ehrlich, ger√§t aber zunehmend unter Druck, weil er den Erwartungen seiner Partnerin nicht gerecht werden kann. Subtiles, zur√ºckgenommenes Spiel ist wichtig.

**Weibliche Nebenrolle**
Junge Frau mit perfekter Au√üenwirkung. Kontrolliert und diszipliniert, privat jedoch angespannt. Die Rolle lebt vom Kontrast zwischen √§u√üerer Kontrolle und innerer Unsicherheit.

**M√§nnliche Nebenrolle**
Charismatisch, dominant, stark auf Au√üenwirkung bedacht. Kontrollierend und schnell reizbar. Muss zwischen Charme und unterschwelliger Bedrohlichkeit wechseln k√∂nnen.

Schauspielerfahrung ist willkommen, aber keine Voraussetzung. Wichtig sind Verl√§sslichkeit, Lust auf Spielen und Interesse an einem emotionalen, beziehungszentrierten Stoff.
Bei Interesse einfach eine Nachricht schreiben, dann schicken wir weitere Infos und das Drehbuch.

Insgesamt zu vergeben sind 4 Rollen, davon 

3 m√§nnliche Hauptrollen (Ben, Nick & Frank) sowie
1 m√§nnliche Nebenrolle (Pablo).

Worum geht‚Äôs im Film?
Ben und Nick sitzen in der Klemme. Sie haben den Bank√ºberfall wie geplant durchgezogen aber am vereinbarten Treffpunkt taucht niemand auf. Mit zwei Geiseln an der Backe m√ºssen sie feststellen, 
dass Geld nicht alle ihre Probleme l√∂st.

items.text:
****CASTING CALL SHORT FILM****

**TITLE: PURPLE INK**

**SYNOPSIS: **The film tells the story of Chase, a teenager with undiagnosed juvenile arthritis, who makes an unlikely friendship with Daren, an old man, during his time at physical therapy.

It is a hopeful story that explores friendship, the acceptance of one's body, and aims to shed light on the disabled youth community, especially those with invisible disabilities that may go undiagnosed or untreated for many years. I grew up with the disease, which greatly limited my mobility and quality of life. Over 300k kids in the US today have some sort of rheumatoid disability, with a large number of them going undiagnosed and untreated. I hope that this film will help destigmatize and bring awareness to what youth disabilities can look like.

**Tentative Filming Dates:** August 26th-30th, 2026

Production Locations: Boston Area

Union + Non-Union. UNPAID. Actors will receive 3 on-set meals and will be compensated for travel and housing.

Project Length: 4 days 

**Please email headshot, reel, and self-tape to [colin_dowse@emerson.edu](mailto:colin_dowse@emerson.edu)

***ROLES:***

**CHASE **Male-Presenting, Any Ethnicity, 16-22 years old

Deeply introspective, Chase has juvenile arthritis and struggles with walking and pain in his lower body. He thinks this holds him back, but in reality, it makes him uncommonly observant and wise for his age. He's smart as a whip and a big classic rock fan, which helps him bond with Daren, his elderly counterpart, who helps him to accept his body for what it is and learn to love himself.

**DAREN **Male-Presenting, Any Ethnicity, 60-80 years old

A soft-spoken retired fishing captain who is admitted to physical therapy due to hip troubles. His health issues place a strain on his relationships. Meeting Chase, who struggles similarly, he develops a paternal bond with him, wishing to share his life's wisdom to help him out of his rut. In helping Chase, he learns a lot about himself.

Liebe Produktionen, Produzenten aber auch liebe Agenturen und Filmschaffende in Deutschland:

+++ Der  erste Gagenkatalog f√ºr Kompars*innen und Kleindarsteller*innen ist seit ein paar Tagen √∂ffentlich! +++

Die darin angegebenen Betr√§ge sind Empfehlungen der Initiative Faire Gagen und beruhen auf den Erfahrungen vieler etablierter Filmschaffender und ihren R√ºckmeldungen an unsere Initiative, als auch auf Gespr√§che unsererseits mit Agenturen und Produktionen. 
 
Dabei werden auch schrittweise gew√§hlte Ziele des Katalogs (z.B. von budget-schw√§cheren Produktionen) zu mehr Fairness und damit auch wieder zu h√∂herer Motivation der Filmschaffenden f√ºhren.

Nachweislich kommt es gerade durch etablierte Filmschaffende zu weniger Problemen beim Buchungsprocedere und ganz besonders am Set, als bei st√§ndig neu gecasteten Menschen, die eben oft ganz andere Beweggr√ºnde haben, wie z.B. "einfach mal dabei sein" und dies auch selbst f√ºr eigentlich nicht mehr Faire Gagen. 

Dazu jedoch nur als Beispiel, die bekanntlich  immer h√∂her steigende Zahl von kurzfristigen Buchungs-Absagen und dabei besonders das Nichterscheinen am Drehort ohne Absage, festgebuchter Kompars*innen. 
Besonders letzteres sehen selbstverst√§ndlich auch wir als ein absolutes "No Go" gegen√ºber unseren Produktionen und Agenturen an.

+++ Eine faire Bezahlung aber auch das schrittweise Umdenken bez√ºglich veralteter Setregeln, oder kaum noch nachvollziebarer Buchungsbeschr√§nkungen (Beispiel Altersgrenzen) wird, verbunden mit  einer h√∂heren Wertsch√§tzung gegen√ºber den Filmschaffenden,  nicht nur zu  einem besseren Arbeitsklima f√ºhren, sondern zwangsl√§ufig auch ein Garant f√ºr direkte  Zeit- und Kosteneinsparungen der Produktionen sein. +++

Auch die Agenturen k√∂nnten so zumindest bei dem f√ºr jede Produktion so wichtigen Faktor "Zeit" profitieren und so noch effizienter und professioneller f√ºr ihre zu betreuenden Produktionen arbeiten.
Tats√§chlich werden nur so beide Seiten mittel- und langfristig provitieren. 
Der leider oft voreilig eingesetzte  Rotstift mancher Produktionen hat bereits viele etablierte und zuverl√§ssige Filmschaffende in den letzten  Jahren zwangsl√§ufig verprellt. 

Daher sehen wir auch ganz allgemein, dass eine Philosophie von "Einsparungen" und "Weiter so" (auf einem sich nicht mehr lohnenden Gagen-Niveau) dem deutschen Film eher schaden als n√ºtzen wird.
Produktionen, die sich eh schon an faire Gagen und Zuschl√§ge halten sind hier nat√ºrlich weniger angesprochen. Sie dienen f√ºr uns jedoch als absolut beispielhaft f√ºr alle anderen, denn sie zeigen uns schon seit vielen Jahren sehr eindrucksvoll, dass Fairness und Wertsch√§tzung eben doch ganz einfach funktioniert.

Initiative Faire Gagen.

I am currently Producing a brand new show for Channel 4 in creating an alternative court to resolve your disputes, without the usual costs and delays.

Has a dispute got out of hand?

Do you want to draw a line under a conflict that‚Äôs been going on too long?

In this brand-new series, from the makers of *Long Lost Family,* we‚Äôll open the doors of a fast-track court that will help people settle their civil disputes.

All those who take part will be provided with **free expert legal representation**.

**We are looking for people who would like to sort out a dispute in a swift and legally-binding hearing.**

Why should you take part?
* Do you feel that you are owed money, an apology, or simply justice on a matter?
Perhaps you want a refund on a service you paid for? Maybe you feel an ex-partner or family member has taken more than their fair share? Whatever the issue, big or small, this could be your chance to have your story heard and to reach a final verdict.
* Perhaps the civil court system feels too complex, too costly, or just takes too long.
* Perhaps you‚Äôd like the free advice of some of Britain‚Äôs top lawyers (likely in region of ¬£10,000)

**If you want to apply or have a no obligation conversation with someone to find out more then drop me a message**

NOW ACCEPTING SUBMISSIONS IN THE GREATER LOS ANGELES AREA

SOUTHERN FRIED FUNERAL by J. Dietz Osborne and Nate Eppler

Non union theatre 

Produced by the JFed Players 
As affiliated with the Jewish Federation of the Greater San Gabriel and Pomona Valleys 

Some details:
Callbacks are in-person on Thursday February 12 in Monrovia. 

Rehearsals start February 22 in Monrovia. They will be Monday, Tuesday, Thursday nights and Sunday days, for the most part. 

Tech week begins April 25 or 26. All cast members must be fully available for tech week.

Performances will be at Ahiah Center for Spiritual Living Pasadena and will be:
Saturday, May 2 evening
Sunday, May 3 matinee 
(Wednesday, May 6 - pickup rehearsal)
Thursday, May 7 evening
Saturday, May 9 evening
Sunday, May 10 (Mother's Day) matinee
Sunday, May 10 (Mother's Day) evening show closing

Please only submit if you're available for all tech week, pickup rehearsal, and all performances.

Selected Actors will be asked to submit self tape auditions. Character breakdowns are below. 

[DOROTHY FRYE] 50s/60s female., Dewey Frye‚Äôs widow and the matriarch of the family. Strong-willed, grieving widow but also snarky and fun. Strong actor with great comedic timing. AUTHENTIC SOUNDING MISSISSIPPI OR SOUTHERN ACCENT. Lead

[SAMMY JO FRYE-LEFETTE] 30s, female. the middle child and future president of the Junior League. Maybe some anger issues, wears the pants in the marriage. Strong actor with great comedic timing. AUTHENTIC SOUNDING MISSISSIPPI OR SOUTHERN ACCENT.

[HARLENE FRYE] 30s/40s, female. the oldest child and prodigal daughter. Strong actor with great comedic timing. AUTHENTIC SOUNDING MISSISSIPPI OR SOUTHERN ACCENT

[DEWEY FRYE JR] 20s, male. the youngest child and not the brightest bulb. Strong actor with great comedic timing. AUTHENTIC SOUNDING MISSISSIPPI OR SOUTHERN ACCENT

[DUB FRYE] 50s/60s, male. Dorothy‚Äôs brother-in-law. Charmingly manipulative. Strong actor with great comedic timing. AUTHENTIC SOUNDING MISSISSIPPI OR SOUTHERN ACCENT

[ATTICUS ‚ÄúATTIE‚Äù VAN LEER] 30s/40s, male, family lawyer and on-again off-again love interest of Harlene. Intellectual. Strong actor with great comedic timing. AUTHENTIC SOUNDING MISSISSIPPI OR SOUTHERN ACCENT

[BEECHAM LEFETTE] 30s, male . Sammy Jo‚Äôs husband. Slightly argumentative, doesn't appreciate being misrepresented. Strong actor with great comedic timing. AUTHENTIC SOUNDING MISSISSIPPI OR SOUTHERN ACCENT

[MARTHA ANN FOX] 50s/60s, female. Dorothy‚Äòs best friend, first name pronounced ‚ÄúMarthann." Rather crass and to the point, like Dorothy from Golden Girls. Strong actor with great comedic timing. AUTHENTIC SOUNDING MISSISSIPPI OR SOUTHERN ACCENT

[FAIRY JUNE COOPER] 50s/60s, female. contemporary of Dorothy and Martha Ann; they‚Äôve been friends since high school. Kind of prude and clueless, well meaning. Strong actor with great comedic timing. AUTHENTIC SOUNDING MISSISSIPPI OR SOUTHERN ACCENT

[BENNY CHARLES GREENWOOD] 50s/60s male, best friend of Dewey Frye Sr. Sincere friend to the family. Not a large role, only a few scenes with some dialogue but present throughout

[OZELLA MEEKS] 60s/70s, female. chairwoman of a community committee, a position she does not take lightly. Her life's goal is organizing and planning while following rules. Strong actor with great comedic timing. AUTHENTIC SOUNDING MISSISSIPPI OR SOUTHERN ACCENT

Storyline: Dewey Frye is dead and the rest of his family is left to pick up the pieces ‚Äì that is if they don't kill each other first. Funerals bring out the worst, the best, and the funniest in people, and the Fryes are no exception. A big-hearted comedy about family ‚Äì Southern-style.

Please submit headshots and resumes and availability to JFedProd@gmail.com 

And feel free to spread the word or share with others you think are a good fit.

items.text: The last few years I‚Äôve taken film serious and created a Film IP Named Last of the Force. This would come with episodes and short films from the series, it has taught me a lot and pushed and challenged me. Which is a huge driving force for my personality, I‚Äôve learned more about myself and grew close with my crew and developed a team. Thanks to you all that have assisted with this project and we have more to go before we accomplish the mission. For any filmmakers needing crew to start up your project and vision contact me. The dots always connect Last of the Force coming soon as well as more projects in the pipeline. Enjoy these films out now with a quick search on the tube.
